drawnet.lib.ddl.constraints
Class IsOfKindCheckConstraint

java.lang.Object
  drawnet.lib.ddl.constraints.Constraint
      drawnet.lib.ddl.constraints.CheckConstraint
          drawnet.lib.ddl.constraints.IsOfKindCheckConstraint

public class IsOfKindCheckConstraint
extends CheckConstraint

A Constraint that checks if an element is of a given kind of element.
This check can be done in EXACT or DERIVED mode. The former means that kind of elements must be exactly the same; the latter means that also a derived kind from the given one is valid.
Example:

'ref' is the name of the property (of kind ElementRefPropertyValue) of the current element that points to the element to check;
'kind' is the kind that the element referred by the property must be of;
'mode' is the mode to use for checking (exact kind, here).
